title: Sexy Accountant Calendar
description: Our tax calendar is here to keep you organized and provide a little eye candy of the sexiest accountants on the planet. This calendar features all 12 months of these number crunching crusaders to help keep your affairs straight all year long. We want to bring the fun back in refund, your tax refund that is.

Suitable for: Being right, kung-fu, meandering Not suitable for: Arguing with your wife

title: Theodore Bear
description: Did I ever tell you the one about how I got that great deal on that car, 26 years ago? Yes. But tell us again, it's a good one. This pair is perfect for instilling patience, humor, and a bit of electricity in your day.

title: The Persimmon Brick Road
description: Be brave and take this pair for a stroll around the block to see what happens. Maybe nothing, but maybe something special... just saying. Suitable for: Making moves, teaching others how to dougie, business fabulous.

description: Named after a dear friend and Chilanimal, this is the biggest party in Chile. So grab a piscola and celebrate. These will do great at dancing with Carlita Ochoa, heading to Playa Blanca, and horseback riding.

title: The Chad
description: “There is only one captain of this love boat, and that is The Chad.”  Sport proudly to snag yourself an angel, or two, or three.

title: Thaddeus Constantine III
description: Opulence, this sock has it.  The understated elegance is fit for a king, or a king’s king. Miniature giraffe not included.

title: Suzzany
description: Sorry, not sorry. Any way you slice it, we love our Suzzany. Suitable for chillin’ with your bear on a park bench, or taking your tiger for a walk.

title: Stripe Dreams
description: Understated, yet nuanced... this is the pair that says you've got a lot to offer, but you don't give it away for free. Perfect for traveling business class in sweats, mountain biking, and marathon note-taking.

title: Spelurking
description: You don't need a headlamp to go adventuring (but they are great). Strap this pair on and appreciate all the world has to offer. Yes, even traffic.

title: Socks On Fleek

title: Sockagawea
description: We've been waiting 3 years to name a sock this... and here you have it. The best named sock. Ever. Only wear these if you want to be too clever for your own good, dance in the rain, or cyclecross the Appalachian trail.

description: Named after our creative kitty. When there's a sock design that is just all kinds of crazy, that's normally because Fergus walked across the keyboard... but then again, we love serendipity. Here's to all the cat lovers.

description: Tranquilo, man. It's all good today, so sit back and soak in the SoCal sun, even if you happen to be in Wisconsin. These rays of sunshine are totally gluten free and ready for enjoyment.

These are perfect for being stubborn, taking out the trash, or running an ultra (first one to do so, gets 10 free pairs, promise).

description: Puppies, teenage mustaches, and these matching pair of socks are pretty much the cutest things on the planet.  One for you, one for the little one. If there's one thing we know for sure, it's that #twinning is #winning. So hit the swings and put that tantrum behind you.    The men’s pairs are all sizes 8-12, and the kid’s pairs come in three sizes, ranging from about 18 months to 12 years old.

It has 4-way stretch and is form-fitting, but does not constrict at all. It's also cool to the touch, ultra breathable, moisture-wicking, quick-drying, flat-stitched, and generally amazing. Get ready to replace your entire underwear drawer. Seriously.    SuperFit: Microfiber Polyamide (85%) + Spandex (15%)

title: Cat Daddy
description: This pair may be too fresh for those who have not yet learned how to dougie.  Once you have those moves down, get to work on the Cat Daddy.  Great for stackin’ Krabby patties.

title: Damn Gino
description: Settle down, we know you were right.  But sporting this pair is a little braggy, don’t you think?

title: Extra Dirty
description: … is how we like our martinis. Socks should, however, be washed every once in awhile. Pairs nicely with “A Socktail” for a smooth finish.

title: Kelly Kapowski
description: No Need to fight over this Kelly. Whether you’re a Zack or a Slater, you can have your very own Kapowski.

title: More Cowbell
description: Unfortunately, there’s no sneaking up on people when you have these babies on.  Just like the name implies, your presence will be announced long before you arrive. But that’s OK, because you got the most stylish socks in all the land and you don’t care who knows it.

title: Patrick Periwinkle
description: An homage to our favorite Oregonian writer and the lovable main character of one of her books. Use these magical socks to hex the evil forces that surround you and find love at the bottom of the washing machine.

title: Siberian Tiger
description: Meet El Tigre’s Russian cousin.  He’s just as fierce but with slightly more swagger.

title: Smoke Signal
description: These were originally going to be worn by all the extras in Dances with Wolves ‘til Kevin Costner’s agent’s brother had a conflict. True story.

title: Warm Taos
description: This pair enjoys desert sunsets, gallery walks, and occasionally staying in to peyote and chill.

title: Ash Monday
description: Looks like somebody’s got a case of the Mondays, and we couldn’t be happier about it.

title: Guaranteed Good Fortune
description: Whether you’re pitching a new idea to the board of directors, heading to Vegas for the weekend, or just enjoying a friendly game of full contact golf, this amazing pair will ensure that you come out on top.  Please sport responsibly.

title: Hood To Coast
description: From the treeline to the shoreline, this pair is at home in any landscape. These are great for crushing the competition at work, then taking your talents to the trail.

title: Willionaire
description: You don’t need a million bucks to look like a baller. All it takes is a rad pair of socks and some can-do ‘tude.

title: Fraggle Rock No Show
description: Welcome to the most perfect no-show socks on the planet. Low enough to be invisible in Vans, but grippy enough not to slip down in the heel. All the while, being extremely breathable to eliminate The Stank Foot.
